[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile processing EXIF data via the `exif_from_data_fuzzer`. The overflow occurs [0m    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Trigger: Running the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` on a specifically crafted testcase [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcauses AddressSanitizer to report an out-of-bounds read.[0m                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Observations:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbyte past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap allocation.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was triggered when running the [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer`. The crash occurred in `exif-data.c` during a `memcpy` in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe function `exif_data_load_data_entry`. The patch attempt added new bounds checks[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maround the data offset and size, introduced an allocation for `entry->data`, and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodified recursive EXIF IFD pointer handling to include additional sanity checks. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the build failed with multiple syntax and identifier [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. “expected identifier or ‘[0m[1;39m([0m[39m’”, “unknown type name ‘entry’”, and [0m        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer log reports a heap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m of `exif-data.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow is a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read at an address immediately past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The allocation happened in `RunOneTest`, leading into the EXIF parsing code.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - ASan’s shadow bytes indicate an out-of-bounds read during a `memcpy` call in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe EXIF loader routine.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations from the Crash Log  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Crash site: `__asan_memcpy` → `exif_data_load_data_entry` → [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_content` → `exif_data_new_from_data`.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Variables involved:  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A buffer of [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes was allocated for the EXIF data.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `doff` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m computed as `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The code performed a `memcpy` of size `s` without confirming that `doff + s`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdid not exceed the buffer length.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No guard prevented reading when `doff` was at the very end of the allocated [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt Details  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added two new checks at the start of `exif_data_load_data_entry`:  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`  [0m                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseparately allocated.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adjusted the IFD-pointer switch cases to wrap recursive calls in an `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mo < [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Build Errors After Patching  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The failure persists despite the new boundary check condition.[0m                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo fully understand and localize the root cause of the overflow, the following code[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregions should be reviewed:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **exif_data_load_data_entry** [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m210[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m220[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How are `doff` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize of the entry[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m computed?[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure all paths that lead to the `memcpy` call properly validate that `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39md + [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoff, d + doff + s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` lies within the allocated buffer of length `size`.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Component count and type size computation**:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Examine how component counts and data type sizes multiply to produce `s`.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Check for integer overflows or missing checks when computing `s`.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Recursive directory loading** in **exif_data_load_data_content**:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify that nested IFD pointer offsets [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`o`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and lengths [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ds`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are handled in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall code paths.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that the top-level buffer pointer `d` and its length `ds` are always [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpassed consistently.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Buffer allocation logic**:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Identify where the buffer backing `d` is allocated and how its length [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrelates with `size` in `exif_data_load_data_entry`.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that allocations account for maximum possible tag data sizes and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mredzones.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA detailed audit of these sections, focusing on offset calculations, boundary [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks, and possible integer wrap-around, will help uncover why the overflow [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains despite the new checks.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue arises when running the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` against the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif library. AddressSanitizer reports a heap-buffer-overflow in [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` while copying [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes past the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation. A patch attempt modified the function to use `size_t` for intermediate [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvariables, inserted checks for integer overflow on size computations, and added [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds checks on the data offset [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and total read length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff + s`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. After[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplying the patch, the fuzzer still triggers the same ASan heap-buffer-overflow at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same location, indicating the patch did not eliminate the out-of-bounds access.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A fuzzer test input caused `exif_from_data_fuzzer` to hit an AddressSanitizer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merror in `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min libexif/exif-data.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stacktrace shows a `__asan_memcpy` read of [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes starting at address [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`, which is exactly one byte past the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The call chain is:  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_entry`  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_content`  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data`  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `exif_data_new_from_data`  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in the fuzz harness  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- ASan’s shadow memory indicates the buffer’s redzone is violated, confirming a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti-byte read overflow.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `libexif/exif-data.c`, the variables `s` and `doff` were changed from [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`unsigned int` to `size_t`.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introduced an inner block to compute `fmt_size = [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and guard against zero size or multiplication [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow:  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Return early if `fmt_size == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m` or `entry->components > [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;36m-1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfmt_size`.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Otherwise compute `s = fmt_size * entry->components`.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added a check `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > size - [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;` to ensure the metadata header is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfully inside the buffer.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- For data entries larger than [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes:  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Read the remote offset `roff` via `exif_get_long`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Return early if `roff` is negative or exceeds the total input size.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Assign `doff = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mroff`.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  For entries ≤ [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes, set `doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- New sanity checks:  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m log debug; return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer was rerun with the same test case inputs and [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m iterations.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The AddressSanitizer report remains effectively identical: the overflow still [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs at `exif_data_load_data_entry` on the same allocation boundary.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The summary line still reports a heap-buffer-overflow at line [0m[1;36m219[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mformerly [0m[1;36m213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `exif-data.c`, and the allocation site is unchanged.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The logic in `exif_data_load_data_entry` around computing `s` and `doff` may [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill allow an out-of-bounds read when `s ≤ [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, or for malformed component counts, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffsets, or formats not covered by the new guards.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- How `exif_format_get_size` handles unknown or invalid formats—zero or special [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodes—could affect the computed `s`.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The validity of `entry->components` as read from the buffer, and whether [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madditional validation is needed before use in size calculations.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The branch that handles small data [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s ≤ [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m may bypass offset checks in a way [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat still permits reading past the buffer end.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Downstream code in `exif_data_load_data_content` or in the loop that iterates [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata entries may assume stronger invariants than what the current checks enforce.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any other callers of `exif_data_load_data_entry` that might interact with buffer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointers or lengths differently.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA holistic review should cover the full data-entry parsing path in `exif-data.c`, [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibexif[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpcmgel2h8[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run against the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` harness triggered an [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer “heap-buffer-overflow” in the function `exif_data_load_data_entry`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39min `libexif/exif-data.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The overflow occurs when copying entry data past the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mend of a small heap allocation [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was proposed that:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Converts several local variables from `unsigned int` to `size_t`.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds explicit checks for minimum header size [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, integer overflows, and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds offsets before reading or copying.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses guarded logic to compute the data size `s` and data offset `doff`.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDespite these additional checks, the fuzzing run still aborts with the same ASan [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow at the same location in `exif_data_load_data_entry`, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating that the patch did not fully prevent out-of-bounds memory access.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash report shows:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - AddressSanitizer detecting a read of [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes beginning at address [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`, which is exactly one byte past the end of an allocated [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Stack trace points to `__asan_memcpy` called from `exif_data_load_data_entry`.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The code reads or copies `s` bytes of entry data from offset `doff` inside the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap region without sufficient bounds checks.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key observations:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The entry header is [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes, and fields within that header [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata format, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponent count, and an inline/offset field[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m determine how many bytes to copy and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere those bytes reside.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - In the failing case, these calculations allow `s` bytes at `doff` to exceed the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated buffer, leading to a multi-byte read past the buffer end.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The harness simply calls `exif_data_new_from_data` on arbitrary input blobs; [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe overflow is entirely inside libexif.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modifies `libexif/exif-data.c` in the function [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`. In summary:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Change local types:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```diff[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - unsigned int s, doff;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   + size_t s, doff;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Require at least [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes available for the entry header:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize < [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m || offset > size - [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Compute `s = format_size * components` with overflow and zero-length checks:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   size_t fmt_size = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt_size == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || entry->components == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m ||[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       entry->components > SIZE_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m fmt_size[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   s = fmt_size * entry->components;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Determine `doff`:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, read a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ExifLong`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from `d + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidating that the offset field is fully inside the buffer and that the resulting [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset does not point beyond `size - [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Else, use `doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Check that `doff` is not past the buffer and that `doff + s <= size`.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Only then call `[0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch context in `exif-data.c` around line [0m[1;36m165[0m[39m:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```diff[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--- a/libexif/exif-data.c[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+++ b/libexif/exif-data.c[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m@@ [0m[1;36m-165[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m165[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m @@ static int [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mExifData *data,[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mconst unsigned char *d,[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39munsigned int size, unsigned int offset[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       [0m[39munsigned int s, doff;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    size_t s, doff;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m [0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mentry->tag    = [0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mentry->format = [0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m@@ [0m[1;36m-177[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m35[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m177[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m44[0m[39m @@ static int [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mExifData *data,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[32m"Loading entry 0x%x [0m[32m([0m[32m'%s'[0m[32m)[0m[32m..."[0m[39m, entry->tag,[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mexif_tag_get_name[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->tag[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    s = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * entry->components;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39ms < entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-        doff = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-        [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Ensure the buffer can hold the [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte entry header *[0m[35m/[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize < [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m || offset > size - [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* compute data size with overflow and zero-length check *[0m[35m/[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        size_t fmt_size = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt_size == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || entry->components == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m ||[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            entry->components > SIZE_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m fmt_size[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        s = fmt_size * entry->components;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* determine data offset *[0m[35m/[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* ensure we can read the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field *[0m[35m/[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > size - [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mExifLong[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        ExifLong roff = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                                      data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mroff < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mroff > size - [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        doff = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mroff;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* check start inside buffer *[0m[35m/[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff > size[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* final bounds check: data region must fit within buffer *[0m[35m/[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                 [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%zu > %zu[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                 doff + s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m [0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mentry->data = [0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Result After Patch[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRe-running the same fuzzer input with the patch applied produces the _identical_ [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mASan error:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow still occurs at the same call to `__asan_memcpy` in [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The protected checks do not prevent the out-of-bounds read in this scenario.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The faulty read is still at offset `[0m[1;36m0x24f[0m[39m` in a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte buffer.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo understand the full scope of this overflow and prevent it effectively, review:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Header Parsing Logic**  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte entry header layout and how `offset`, `format`, and `components` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare validated.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **`exif_format_get_size` and Component Multiplication**  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure no unexpected return values or side effects that undermine overflow [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Offset Field Reading [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_get_long`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that signedness or alignment issues cannot bypass the `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mroff < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Call Sites in `exif_data_load_data_content` and `exif_data_load_data`**  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validate higher-level loops and recursion for consistent bounds enforcement.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **`exif_data_alloc` and Subsequent `memcpy`**  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Check that allocation size matches the guarded value `s` and that the pointer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marithmetic used in `memcpy` is always within the valid region.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA holistic review of the data-entry loading sequence, from initial TIFF/EXIF block [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing through tag‐value extraction, will help locate any remaining corner cases [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat allow under- or over-flows to slip past the current guards.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
